snippet.textDisplay: Brilliant composition where the talent of Javed Bashir and the beauty and essence of the qwali part which is the heart of this rendition is portrayed and protected without distorting too much yet brought the powerful voice of Ali Azmat adequately and gave both room to showcase their talent. Amazing. Those who have never played any musical instruments in their life can judge whatever way the want, but this composition was typical coke studio high quality production. Perhaps not amongst the very best but still very very good. Aaqa has still been the best track so far.

snippet.textDisplay: I don't usually comment on anything but i couldnt just let this slip. The following is with all the respect i could muster. Plucked this right off of wikipedia "Music is an art form and cultural activity whose medium is sound and silence." So respect those who make it. In addition, everyone is entitled to their opinion (emphasis on "their") form your own, don't borrow someone elses. As far as this song is concerned, its brilliant. The collab is unusual yet works, the instruments are exquisitely played (coming from a musical background myself), i wish everyone had the right speakers to appreciate the bass working in sync with Javed Bashir's voice and by god his low notes could compete with the bass itself. Ali Azmat was brilliant, he added personality to the song by shamelessly howling and screaming inserts into it and at times even elegance. Also, please watch the BTS for all songs just so that you know what the musicians want YOU to expect from the songs that theyve worked so hard on composing.
